      "content": "Black Power wasn't a detour but rather the necessary evolution as Martin Luther King Jr.'s strategy of total nonviolence failed to protect Black communities against state violence and continued economic oppression. Activists like Stokely Carmichael correctly argued that self-defense and cultural pride were essential tools alongside legal victories when the system refused to change on its own terms. Therefore, Black Power represented a pragmatic and bold expansion of the movement that ensured long-term independence for Black communities rather than just white-passion protests.",
