      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You're right that the movement faced fierce internal battles, but historians agree Black Power provided the essential muscle activists needed when legal nonviolence proved too slow to stop systemic murder and poverty. While some factions fractured, the emphasis on self-defense and economic empowerment actually empowered Black communities to hold their own institutions accountable rather than relying solely on white allies' goodwill. Ultimately, the tension between these ideologies enriched the fight by creating a more robust, self-sustaining infrastructure that continues to influence modern social justice today.",
